metadata.name: DA poverty estimation dataset
metadata.description: Socioeconomic indicators like poverty rates, population change, unemployment rates, and education levels vary geographically across U.S. States and counties. This dataset includes poverty indicators across different counties across all states of the US.

metadata.name: FIPS
metadata.description: Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) are numeric codes assigned to US states and counties

metadata.name: State
metadata.description: State of US

metadata.name: Area
metadata.description: Area name (typically county)

metadata.name: RUCCode
metadata.description: Rural-Urban Continuum Codes, a classification scheme that distinguishes metropolitan counties

metadata.name: POVALL_2016
metadata.description: Estimate of people of all ages in poverty in 2016
